Deputy National Security Advisor Anne Neuberger spoke about the need for organizations to be on guard for cyber threats, especially over holiday weekends when attackers may target understaffed security operation centers. She encouraged organizations to update and patch all software, ensure strong passwords and implement multifactor authentication. Neuberger also emphasized the importance of reviewing incident response plans, maintaining up-to-date backups, and being vigilant for phishing emails and unusual links. She mentioned the efforts of the Biden administration to address cyber threats and the recent meeting with technology executives to improve cybersecurity measures. Neuberger also discussed ongoing discussions with Russia regarding cyber activity and efforts to improve the cybersecurity of federal networks.